com%2Fblog%2Frental-market%2Fmarket-snapshots%2Ftop-renting-sweet-spots-us%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERentCafe%20blog%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20stated%20that%20%26quot%3Bto%20obtain%20the%20ratios%20used%20in%20the%20score%20for%20each%20category%20in%20each%20city%2C%20we%20calculated%20the%20disposable%20income%20left%20after%20paying%20the%20monthly%20rent.%20We%20then%20aggregated%20the%20price%20per%20unit%20for%20each%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20products%20and%20services%20and%20calculated%20the%20ratio%20between%20income%20and%20total%20cost%20per%20category.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoug%20Ressler%2C%20manager%20of%20business%20intelligence%20at%20Yardi%20Matrix%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20overall%20score%20%26quot%3Bwas%20based%20on%20the%20sum%20of%20all%26quot%3B%20weighted%20category%20scores.%20Some%20categories%20had%20a%20larger%20weight%20than%20others%3B%20the%20income-to-rent%20ratio%20had%20the%20largest%20weight%2C%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20hover%20over%20each%20city%20in%20the%20chart%20below%20to%20see%20the%20values%20from%20RentCafe%20that%20were%20shared%20with%20BI%2C%20including%20each%20city's%20overall%20score.%20The%20overall%20score%20is%20also%20seen%20by%20the%20size%20of%20each%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fmq3h7%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22How%20income%20compares%20to%20expenses%20by%20city%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20seen%20in%20the%20chart%2C%20looking%20just%20at%20monthly%20renter%20household%20income%20compared%20to%20monthly%20rent%20and%20basic%20necessities%20together%2C%20many%20of%20the%20places%20looked%20at%20had%20ratios%20around%201.%20That%20is%2C%20incomes%20weren't%20too%20far%20off%20from%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERentCafe%20found%20Athens%2C%20Georgia%3B%20New%20Orleans%3B%20Albany%2C%20New%20York%3B%20and%20Gainesville%2C%20Florida%2C%20had%20some%20of%20the%20lower%20scores%20among%20the%20places%20examined.%20They%20all%20had%20scores%20that%20were%20less%20than%2018%2C%20meaning%20they%20are%20among%20the%20locations%20where%20renters%20might%20not%20be%20able%20to%20get%20a%20lot%20out%20of%20their%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAuburn%2C%20Alabama%2C%20had%20a%20score%20far%20lower%20than%20the%20other%20places%2C%20with%20a%20score%20of%201.59.%20Its%20monthly%20income%20was%20%241%2C880.%20Rent%20and%20the%20various%20expenses%20together%20had%20a%20value%20of%20%242%2C585%20for%20this%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Sunnyvale%20didn't%20have%20the%20largest%20monthly%20rent%20and%20basic%20necessities%20value%20together%2C%20it%20did%20have%20the%20highest%20monthly%20renter%20household%20income%20among%20the%20189%20US%20cities%20part%20of%20the%20analysis.%20Its%20monthly%20income%20was%20more%20than%20%2412%2C000.%20Its%20rent%20is%20around%20a%20quarter%20of%20that%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eat%20around%20%243%2C000%20a%20month%20per%20the%20blog%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rentcafe.com%2Fblog%2Frental-market%2Fmarket-snapshots%2Ftop-renting-sweet-spots-us%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%20from%20RentCafe%3C%2Fa%3E%20writer%20Alexandra%20Both%20that%20highlighted%20the%20analysis%20stated%20that%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20heart%20of%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20renters%20had%20the%20highest%20annual%20wages%20in%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20triple%20the%20nation's%20median%20income.%26quot%3B%20The%20post%20noted%20%2449%2C201%20as%20the%20median%20for%20renters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Both%20wrote%20that%20%26quot%3BBoston%20had%20similar%20prices%20for%20basic%20necessities%26quot%3B%20as%20well%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20slightly%20higher%20monthly%20rent%26quot%3B%20than%20for%20Sunnyvale.%20However%2C%20Both%20added%20%26quot%3Bits%20lower%20annual%20income%20of%20just%20less%20than%20%2461%2C000%20would%20make%20budgeting%20more%20challenging%20for%20renters.%26quot%3B%20Boston's%20score%20based%20on%20the%20methodology%20was%208.85.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManhattan%20had%20the%20largest%20monthly%20rent%20plus%20basic%20necessities%20value%20but%20ended%20up%20having%20one%20of%20the%20lower%20scores%2C%20at%2014.73.%20Its%20monthly%20renter%20household%20income%20was%20only%20around%20a%20%24500%20difference%20from%20rent%20and%20basic%20necessities%20analyzed%2C%20or%20%246%2C477%20compared%20to%20%245%2C965.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20the%20scores%20calculated%20using%20income%2C%20rent%2C%20and%20expenses%20data%2C%20three%20of%20the%20top%2015%20cities%20where%20income%20can%20go%20far%20were%20in%20Texas%2C%20with%20scores%20near%20or%20over%2060.0.%20Two%20of%20the%20top%205%20cities%20were%20in%20Virginia%2C%20with%20scores%20not%20too%20far%20from%20or%20greater%20than%2070.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FR4wfz%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Top%20cities%20where%20RentCafe%20finds%20income%20can%20stretch%20the%20furthest%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22947%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20the%20rental%20market%20looks%20like%20and%20may%20look%20like%20this%20year%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Ressler%20noted%20the%20attractiveness%20of%20city%20hubs%20is%20partly%20behind%20why%20there%20could%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20supply%20coming%20in%20those%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20coastal%20cities%2C%20the%20gateway%20cities%20have%20always%20been%20hubs%20for%20greater%20density%2C%26quot%3B%20Ressler%20said.%20%26quot%3BWith%20greater%20density%2C%20you%20have%20more%20population%2C%20you%20have%20