0greenery%2C%20rolling%20hills%2C%20and%20streams%20in%20his%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMike%20said%20meeting%20new%20people%20and%20making%20friends%20in%20Kansas%20is%20a%20lot%20easier.%20As%20a%20car%20enthusiast%20whose%20friends%20moved%20away%20from%20the%20Bay%20Area%2C%20he%20joined%20a%20group%20of%20a%20dozen%20locals%20who%20meet%20weekly%20to%20discuss%20and%20check%20out%20cars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20easier%20to%20live%20here.%20The%20streets%20are%20wider%2C%20the%20traffic%20is%20less%20aggressive%2C%20no%20one's%20laying%20on%20the%20horn%20or%20road%20raging%2C%26quot%3B%20Mike%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20his%20community%20reminded%20him%20of%20Minnesota.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20has%20no%20intention%20of%20moving%20out%20of%20Kansas%2C%20noting%20that%20his%20experience%20so%20far%20has%20been%20a%20pleasant%20surprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20a%20California%20basher%20because%20California%20had%20been%20very%20good%20to%20me%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20beautiful%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20Mike%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20miss%20the%20palm%20trees%20and%20being%20near%20the%20ocean%20and%20seeing%20the%20bay%20every%20day%2C%20but%20that%20wasn't%20enough%20to%20keep%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20recently%20moved%20to%20a%20new%20state%20or%20moved%20out%20of%20the%20US%20to%20a%20different%20country%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ansheidlower%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ensheidlower%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-california-kansas-pros-cons-san-francisco-weather-buying-home-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709636701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65553ac022cf74a573981f67%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-california-kansas-pros-cons-san-francisco-weather-buying-home-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20boomer%20and%20his%20wife%20moved%20to%20Kansas%20after%20living%20in%20California%20for%2050%20years%2C%20noting%20it's%20much%20easier%20to%20make%20friends%20and%20costs%20are%20lower.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40insider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-california-kansas-pros-cons-san-francisco-weather-buying-home-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BHiding%20Info%26quot%3B%3A%20Congress%20On%20SBI%20Seeking%20More%20Time%20For%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Data%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20day%20after%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20requested%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20extend%20the%20deadline%20for%20giving%20information%20about%20donations%20made%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20the%20Congress%20has%20hit%20out%20at%20the%20BJP%20and%20said%20the%20party%20is%20using%20the%20bank%20as%20a%20shield%20to%20hide%20the%20details.%20With%20the%20SBI%20seeking%20an%20extension%20till%20June%2030%20-%20as%20against%20the%20court's%20deadline%20of%20March%206%20-%20the%20Congress%20has%20also%20accused%20the%20BJP%20of%20trying%20to%20keep%20the%20data%20on%20the%20%26quot%3Bunconstitutional%20bonds%26quot%3B%20under%20wraps%20until%20after%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNot%20unexpectedly%2C%20but%20in%20a%20very%20shocking%20and%20brazen%20way%2C%20the%20SBI%20has%20approached%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20has%20sought%20time%20until%20June%2030.%20SBI%20is%20not%20just%20India's%20largest%20lender%2C%20it%20is%20a%20fully%20computerised%20bank.%20It%20operates%2048%20crore%20bank%20accounts%2C%2066%2C000%20ATMs%20and%20has%20nearly%2023%2C000%20branches%20all%20over%20the%20country%20and%20beyond%20India.%20And%20this%20SBI%20needs%20five%20months%20to%20give%20data%20on%20just%2022%2C217%20electoral%20bonds.%20It%20can%20get%20this%20information%20in%20a%20click.%20Why%20is%20the%20BJP%20so%20scared%20of%20these%20names%20coming%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Congress%20leader%20Supriya%20Shrinate%20asked%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Shrinate%20said%20about%20Rs%2012%2C000%20crore%20was%20collected%20by%20parties%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20between%202017%20and%202023%20and%20%26quot%3Btwo-thirds%26quot%3B%20of%20that%2C%20or%20nearly%20Rs%206%2C500%20crore%2C%20went%20to%20the%20BJP%20while%20the%20Congress%20got%20a%20%26quot%3Bmeasly%26quot%3B%209%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDo%20people%20in%20this%20democracy%20not%20have%20a%20right%20to%20know%20who%20is%20donating%20to%20which%20party%2C%20and%20how%20much%2C%20and%20at%20what%20time%3F%20Is%20there%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%3F%20SBI%20woke%20up%20after%2020-25%20days%20and%20realised%20it%20needs%20additional%20time.%20There%20is%20a%20clear%20attempt%20by%20the%20SBI%20and%20the%20government%20of%20India%20to%20conceal%20the%20names%20of%20donors%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20alleged.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20landmark%20judgment%20on%20February%2015%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20declared%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20unconstitutional%20and%20said%20that%20it%20violates%20the%20citizens'%20right%20to%20information.%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20had%20also%20said%20that%20the%20scheme%20was%20unconstitutional%20and%20arbitrary%2C%20and%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%20arrangement%20between%20political%20parties%20and%20donors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsking%20the%20SBI%20to%20stop%20issuing%20the%20bonds%20immediately%2C%20the%20court%20had%20ordered%20the%20bank%20to%20give%20details%20of%20donations%20made%20through%20this%20mode%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20by%20March%206.%20The%20poll%20panel%20was%20asked%20to%20publish%20the%20information%20on%20its%20website%20by%20March%2013.%20The%20SBI%20approached%20the%20court%20on%20Monday%20and%20sought%20an%20extension%20of%20the%20deadline%20till%20June%2030.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709636640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fo4h8qs_supriya-shrinate_625x300_05_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhiding-info-congress-on-sbi-seeking-more-time-for-electoral-bonds-data-5180748%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20day%20after%20the%20SBI%20requested%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20extend%20the%20deadline%20for%20giving%20information%20about%20donations%20made%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20the%20Congress%20has%20hit%20out%20at%20the%20BJP%20and%20said%20the%20party%20is%20using%20the%20bank%20as%20a%20shield%20to%20hide%20the%20details.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhiding-info-congress-on-sbi-seeking-more-time-for-electoral-bonds-data-5180748%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhiding-info-congress-on-sbi-seeking-more-time-for-electoral-bonds-data-5180748%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fhiding-info-congress-on-sbi-seeking-more-time-for-electoral-bonds-data-5180748%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20rise%20of%20the%20job-search%20bots%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Robots%20filling%20out%20stacks%20of%20resumes.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e5fe6290413ab8e1d8e1d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EHugo%20Herrera%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20fall%20of%202020%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20in%20unfamiliar%20territory%3A%20I%20was%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20job.%20In%20theory%2C%20it%20was%20something%20I%20should%20have%20known%20a%20lot%20about%20as%20an%20economics%20reporter.%20But%20in%20practice%2C%20I%20was%20lost.%20Because%20I%20had%20stumbled%20into%20a%20great%20job%20right%20out%20of%20college%2C%20and%20stayed%20with%20that%20company%20for%20a%20decade%2C%20I%20was%20blissfully%20unaware%20of%20how%20soul-crushing%20it%20was%20to%20be%20a%20job%20seeker%20in%2021st-century%20corporate%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20threw%20myself%20into%20the%20task.%20I%20meticulously%20researched%20employers.%20I%20applied%20to%20a%20dozen%20openings.%20I%20tailored%20my%20CV%20to%20match%20each%20job%20description.%20I%20wrote%20heartfelt%20paragraphs%20about%20why%20each%20role%20was%20perfect%20for%20me.%20Yet%20all%20I%20got%20back%20was%20a%20raft%20of%20canned%20rejection%20emails%20%E2%80%94%20or%20worse%2C%20silence.%20I%20was%20floored%20that%20I%20didn't%20advance%20to%20a%20single%20interview.%20%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20terrible%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20I%20thought.%20%3Cem%3EHow%20does%20anyone%20do%20this%3F%20%3C%2Fem%3EI%20might%20as%20well%20have%20been%20sending%20my%20applications%20out%20into%20the%20ether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuckily%2C%20I%20landed%20a%20job%20after%20a%20few%20months.%20But%20the%20experience%20stayed%20with%20me.%20And%20these%20days%2C%20applying%20for%20a%20job%20has%20turned%20into%20even%20more%20of%20a%20nightmare.%20In%20the%20current%20market%2C%20it's%20not%20uncommon%20for%20totally%20unremarkable%20jobs%20to%20attract%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-wfh-jobs-application-odds-tech-market-rto-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ethousands%20%3C%2Fem%3Eof%20applications%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Employers%20are%20so%20overwhelmed%20by%20the%20flood%20of%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20that%20they're%20barely%20able%20to%20glance%20at%20most%20of%20them%2C%20let%20alone%20read%20them.%20The%20whole%20process%20has%20become%20an%20odds%20game%3A%20Job%20seekers%20submit%20their%20cover%20letters%20to%20hundreds%20of%20companies%2C%20struggling%20to%20stand%20out%20among%20the%20tsunami%20of%20applicants.%20Things%20have%20gotten%20so%20grim%20that%20LinkedIn%20no%20longer%20trumpets%20the%20number%20of%20people%20who%20have%20applied%20to%20openings%20on%20its%20job%20portal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20I%20heard%20that%20you%20can%20now%20use%20a%20bot%20to%20mass-apply%20to%20job%20openings%2C%20I%20was%20intrigued.%20The%20bots%20%E2%80%94%20with%20names%20like%20LazyApply%20and%20Massive%20%E2%80%94%20have%20turned%20job%20hunting%20into%20a%20technological%20arms%20race.%20You%20pay%20a%20fee%2C%20feed%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20into%20the%20bot%2C%20tell%20it%20what%20you're%20looking%20for%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Eblam!%20%E2%80%94%20%3C%2Fem%3Eit%20starts%20sending%20out%20hundreds%20of%20applications%20on%20your%20behalf%2C%20often%20in%20real%20time.%20It's%20the%20promise%20of%20AI%2C%20applied%20to%20the%20job%20market%3A%20an%20intelligent%2C%20personalized%2C%20HR-slaying%20machine%2C%20designed%20to%20land%20you%20a%20gig%20through%20a%20combination%20of%20tech-savvy%20and%20brute%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20is%3A%20Do%20the%20bots%20work%3F%20I%20decided%20to%20find%20out.%20So%20I%20went%20undercover%20in%20the%20age%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20looking%20for%20a%20job.%20But%20late%20one%20night%20I%20cracked%20open%20a%20beer%2C%20updated%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20pulled%20out%20my%20credit%20card%2C%20and%20entrusted%20my%20fate%20to%20a%20job-application%20bot.%20Which%20roles%20would%20it%20apply%20to%3F%20How%20accurately%20would%20it%20reflect%20my%20skills%20and%20interests%20to%20employers%3F%20A%20friend%20joked%2C%20%26quot%3BDoes%20your%20editor%20know%20this%20story%20might%20end%20in%20you%20taking%20a%20new%20role%3F%26quot%3B%20The%20thought%20hadn't%20even%20crossed%20my%20mind.%20I%20didn't%20think%20any%20employers%20would%20actually%20bite.%20How%20could%20an%20AI-generated%20version%20of%20me%20possibly%20compete%20in%20such%20a%20crowded%20and%20chaotic%20job%20market%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20120%20applications%20later%2C%20I%20stood%20corrected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20bot%20I%20tried%20was%20called%20Sonara.%20For%20%2479.99%20a%20month%2C%20I%20signed%20up%20for%20the%20most%20expensive%20%26quot%3Bamplitude%26quot%3B%20plan%2C%20which%20would%20allow%20me%20to%20apply%20for%20420%20openings.%20After%20I%20spent%20a%20half%20hour%20uploading%20my%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20and%20completing%20my%20profile%2C%20Sonara%20showed%20me%20maybe%20a%20dozen%20job%20options.%20I%20greenlighted%20a%20few%20of%20them%2C%20and%20the%20bot%20promised%20it%20would%20send%20them%20out.%20Each%20morning%20when%20I%20logged%20back%20on%2C%20it%20would%20send%20me%20a%20trickle%20of%20new%20options%20to%20consider.%20But%20the%20ones%20I%20approved%20continued%20to%20sit%20in%20the%20queue%2C%20unsent.%20It%20was%20hardly%20the%20job-applying%20firehose%20I%20was%20looking%20for.%20I%20pinged%20customer%20service%20a%20few%20times.%20Then%2C%20after%20a%20week%2C%20a%20statement%20popped%20up%20on%20Sonara's%20website.%20The%20service%20was%20shutting%20down.%20%3Cem%3EGreat%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20I%20thought.%20%3Cem%3EThere%20goes%20my%20%2479.99.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUndeterred%2C%20I%20signed%20up%20for%20WonsultingAI%2C%20which%20seemed%20like%20a%20bargain%20at%20only%20%2419.99%20a%20month.%20It%20was%20a%20little%20more%20manual%20than%20Sonara%3A%20Every%20time%20I%20wanted%20it%20to%20pull%20in%20more%20job%20openings%2C%20I%20had%20to%20input%20my%20experience%20level%20and%20specify%20the%20title%20and%20location%20of%20the%20position%20I%20was%20looking%20for.%20It%20had%20a%20cool%20feature%20that%20allowed%20me%20to%20use%20a%20different%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20for%20each%20job%20title%20I%20applied%20to%2C%20meaning%20I%20could%20highlight%20different%20skills%20and%20achievements%20for%20various%20positions.%20But%20like%20Sonara%2C%20it%20didn't%20show%20me%20many%20job%20openings%2C%20and%20it%20was%20pretty%20glitchy.%20About%20one%20in%20three%20applications%20never%20went%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20robot%20carrying%20resumes.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e5feb6ce7f1785b2e5f781%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EHugo%20Herrera%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20more%20hope%20for%20Massive%2C%20another%20bot%20I%20tried.%20True%20to%20its%20name%2C%20it%20showed%20me%20way%20more%20openings%20than%20Sonara%20and%20Wonsulting.%20But%20it%20had%20a%20limited%2C%20preset%20list%20of%20corporate%20occupations%20I%20could%20apply%20to.%20I%20chose%20a%20couple%20that%20felt%20most%20relevant%20to%20what%20I%20do%3A%20content%20marketing%20and%20PR.%20For%20%2439%20a%20month%2C%20it%20would%20send%20out%20up%20to%2050%20applications%20a%20week.%20Every%20few%20days%2C%20I%20would%20spend%2020%20minutes%20sifting%20through%20the%20options%20and%20vetoing%20the%20jobs%20that%20weren't%20relevant.%20It%20all%20seemed%20pretty%20seamless.%20After%20a%20few%20days%2C%20I%20started%20getting%20a%20steady%20stream%20of%20automated%20emails%20from%20various%20employers%20thanking%20me%20for%20submitting%20my%20application.%20Still%2C%2050%20applications%20a%20week%20felt%20pretty%20tame%20in%20the%20AI%20age.%20What%20I%20wanted%20was%20a%20true%20spray-and-pray%20machine%2C%20the%20AK-47%20of%20job-application%20bots.%20For%20that%2C%20I%20turned%20to%20LazyApply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELazyApply%20didn't%20offer%20a%20monthly%20subscription%20option%2C%20so%20I%20purchased%20a%20lifetime%20plan%20for%20%24129.%20That%20gave%20me%20the%20ability%20to%20submit%20a%20maximum%20of%20750%20applications%20%3Cem%3Eper%20day.%20%3C%2Fem%3E(A%20more%20expensive%20plan%20came%20with%20unlimited%20applications%2C%20but%20I%20just%20couldn't%20imagine%20sending%20out%20more%20than%20750%20in%20a%20week%2C%20let%20alone%20a%20day.)%20Unlike%20the%20other%20bots%2C%20which%20ingested%20job%20openings%20into%20their%20own%20sites%2C%20LazyApply%20submitted%20applications%20via%20external%20job%20boards.%20So%20I%20linked%20my%20brand-new%20LazyApply%20profile%20to%20my%20accounts%20on%20Indeed%2C%20ZipRecruiter%2C%20and%20LinkedIn.%20Then%20I%20set%20it%20loose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20other%20bots%2C%20LazyApply%20did%20all%20the%20applying%20in%20real%20time%2C%20right%20in%20front%20of%20my%20eyes.%20It%20was%20as%20if%20someone%20had%20hacked%20my%20computer%3A%20I%20watched%20as%20the%20bot%20clicked%20on%20various%20boxes%20and%20typed%20out%20answers%20to%20short%20questions.%20For%20the%20first%20few%20minutes%2C%20I%20was%20mesmerized.%20Then%2C%20I%20started%20to%20panic.%20In%20one%20application%2C%20the%20bot%20indicated%20that%20I%20speak%20conversational-level%20Spanish%2C%20which%20I%20definitely%20do%20not.%20In%20another%2C%20it%20reported%20that%20I%20was%20African%20American%2C%20even%20though%20I%20had%20specified%20in%20my%20LazyApply%20profile%20that%20I%20am%20Asian.%20I%20shouldn't%20have%20been%20surprised%2C%20given%20AI's%20well-known%20propensity%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatbot-chatgpt-google-microsofty-lying-search-belief-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20stuff%20up%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20I%20was%20alarmed.%20If%20I%20had%20been%20a%20real%20job%20seeker%2C%20I%20probably%20would%20have%20pulled%20the%20plug%20on%20the%20rogue%20machine.%20Instead%2C%20I%20let%20LazyApply%20do%20its%20thing.%20I%20was%20curious%20to%20see%20which%20jobs%2C%20if%20any%2C%20Spanish-speaking%20African%20American%20Aki%20would%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20things%20got%20even%20weirder.%20A%20few%20applications%20in%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20LazyApply%20wasn't%20using%20the%20updated%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20I%20had%20given%20it.%20Instead%2C%20it%20was%20attaching%20a%20document%20I%20didn't%20recognize%2C%20titled%20%26quot%3BAki%20Ito%20Cover%20Letter%2C%20Resume%2C%20Links%20for%20Insider.pdf.%26quot%3B%20%3Cem%3EThat's%20strange%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20I%20thought.%20%3Cem%3EDid%20LazyApply%20auto-generate%20a%20cover%20letter%20for%20me%3F%20%3C%2Fem%3EI%20wondered%20whether%20it%20was%20any%20good.%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EBut%20when%20I%20opened%20the%20PDF%2C%20I%20saw%20it%20was%20dated%20October%2024%2C%202020.%20It%20read%3A%20%26quot%3BDear%20Mr.%20Carlson%3A%20I'm%20writing%20to%20apply%20for%20the%20analytical%20features%20editor%20position%20at%20Insider.%26quot%3B%20Instead%20of%20sending%20out%20the%20updated%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20I'd%20provided%2C%20LazyApply%20was%20submitting%20an%20old%20cover%20letter%20it%20had%20found%20buried%20in%20the%20depths%20of%20my%20LinkedIn%20account%2C%20from%20when%20I%20had%20applied%20to%20BI%20three%20years%20ago.%20In%20a%20single%20spurt%2C%2027%20employers%20%E2%80%94%20ranging%20from%20a%20website%20I%20had%20never%20heard%20of%20called%20CryptoNewsZ%20to%20venerable%20publications%20like%20The%20Boston%20Globe%20%E2%80%94%20received%20an%20application%20from%20me%20that%20talked%20about%20how%20much%20I%20wanted%20to%20work%20for%20one%20of%20their%20competitors.%20LazyApply%2C%20I%20realized%20in%20horror%2C%20was%20living%20up%20to%20its%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EApplying%20for%20jobs%20has%20never%20been%20easy%2C%20or%20pleasant.%20Nobody%20liked%20it%20back%20in%20the%20old%20days%2C%20when%20people%20found%20work%20by%20scanning%20the%20classified%20ads%20in%20their%20local%20newspaper%2C%20going%20to%20Kinko's%20to%20print%20out%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%2C%20mailing%20off%20their%20applications%2C%20and%20then%20waiting%20weeks%20or%20months%20to%20hear%20back.%20Looking%20for%20work%20has%20always%20been%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20internet%20promised%20to%20change%20all%20that.%20Three%20decades%20ago%2C%20when%20Monster%20and%20CareerBuilder%20launched%2C%20they%20sought%20to%20match%20huge%20pools%20of%20job%20seekers%20and%20employers%20in%20one%20big%20forum%20%E2%80%94%20to%20create%20what's%20known%2C%20in%20economics%2C%20as%20a%20thicker%20market.%20With%20more%20efficient%20matchmaking%20between%20companies%20and%20prospective%20employees%2C%20the%20thinking%20went%2C%20we%20might%20even%20be%20able%20to%20permanently%20lower%20unemployment%20and%20boost%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20thicker%20market%20actually%20didn't%20make%20the%20matching%20process%20any%20more%20efficient.%20Employers%20got%20access%20to%20a%20larger%20pool%20of%20applicants%2C%20but%20they%20didn't%20have%20the%20tools%20to%20sort%20through%20the%20sudden%20influx%20of%20options.%20Besieged%20by%20volume%2C%20they%20coped%20by%20spending%20less%20time%20reviewing%20the%20details%20of%20every%20applicant%20and%20ghosting%20the%20ones%20they%20rejected.%20Candidates%20adapted%20by%20sending%20out%20more%20applications%2C%20which%20further%20overwhelmed%20HR%20departments.%20The%20new%20technology%20came%20with%20an%20ironic%20twist%3A%20It%20made%20it%20easier%20than%20ever%20to%20apply%20for%20a%20job%2C%20and%20harder%20than%20ever%20to%20actually%20land%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20wave%20of%20AI%20was%20supposed%20to%20fix%20what%20the%20internet%20broke.%20Job%20boards%20began%20to%20take%20on%20a%20more%20active%20role%20in%20the%20marketplace%2C%20using%20big%20data%20to%20recommend%20the%20best%20jobs%20to%20job%20seekers%20and%20the%20best%20job%20seekers%20to%20employers.%20A%20decade%20ago%2C%20when%20I%20was%20writing%20for%20Bloomberg%2C%20I%20posited%20that%20the%20new%20approach%20might%20finally%20solve%20what%20one%20economist%20called%20the%20job%20market's%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2013-04-03%2Falgorithms-play-matchmaker-to-fight-7-7-u-s-unemployment-jobs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eneedle-in-the-haystack%20problem%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20I%20couldn't%20have%20been%20more%20wrong.%20The%20vicious%20cycle%20continued%2C%20forcing%20everyone%20to%20apply%20to%20ever%20more%20jobs%20as%20their%20chances%20of%20success%20dropped.%20Hence%20the%20bots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20microscope%20reveals%20a%20robot%20face%20where%20a%20human%20face%20appears%20on%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e5ff076080194819fc32a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EHugo%20Herrera%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20though%2C%20it%20looks%20like%20the%20arrival%20of%20job%20bots%20is%20only%20making%20the%20problem%20worse.%20For%20starters%2C%20employers%20hate%20them.%20HR%20departments%20have%20no%20way%20of%20knowing%20which%20applications%20came%20from%20a%20human%20and%20which%20came%20from%20a%20machine.%20Unless%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20bot%20screws%20up%2C%20like%20LazyApply%20did%20on%20my%20applications.%20Factual%20errors%2C%20nonsensical%20answers%20to%20questions%2C%20false%20promises%20of%20Spanish%20fluency%20%E2%80%94%20letting%20a%20bot%20do%20your%20job%20hunting%20can%20make%20you%20look%20really%2C%20really%20bad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20definitely%20a%20huge%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Tony%20Riggins%2C%20who%20has%20years%20of%20experience%20as%20a%20recruiter%20for%20leading%20tech%20companies.%20%26quot%3BIt%20can%20completely%20damage%20your%20candidacy%2C%20and%20perhaps%20even%20your%20reputation%2C%20if%20you're%20a%20candidate%20with%20an%20application%20making%20mistakes.%26quot%3B%20Thanks%20to%20LazyApply%2C%20I've%20probably%20destroyed%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eany%20chance%20I%20had%20of%20working%20for%20The%20Boston%20Globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20bot%20services%20are%20aware%20of%20their%20technology's%20limitations.%20Their%20solution%20is%20the%20same%20one%20that%20tech%20platforms%20like%20Facebook%20and%20YouTube%20have%20long%20been%20forced%20to%20resort%20to%20in%20the%20face%20of%20their%20algorithmic%20chaos%3A%20reintroducing%20a%20layer%20of%20human%20oversight%20to%20the%20process.%20Massive%20relies%20on%20human%20%26quot%3Bjob%20experts%26quot%3B%20to%20double-check%20every%20application%20completed%20by%20its%20bot.%20Other%20services%2C%20including%20Teal%20and%20Simplify%2C%20use%20Chrome%20extensions%20that%20make%20%3Cem%3Eyou%20%3C%2Fem%3Eresponsible%20for%20reviewing%20the%20bot's%20work%2C%20forcing%20you%20to%20click%20%26quot%3Bsubmit%26quot%3B%20before%20each%20autofilled%20application%20is%20sent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELadders%2C%20a%20job%20board%20that%20specializes%20in%20high-paid%20positions%2C%20takes%20human%20oversight%20a%20step%20further.%20Early%20in%20the%20pandemic%2C%20when%20hiring%20came%20to%20a%20standstill%2C%20the%20company%20brainstormed%20new%20ways%20to%20help%20job%20seekers.%20%26quot%3BA%20top%20complaint%20over%20and%20over%20again%20was%2C%20'It%20takes%20me%20too%20long%20to%20apply%20for%20all%20these%20jobs%2C'%26quot%3B%20recalls%20Marc%20Cenedella%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20executive%20chair%20of%20Ladders.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20mind-numbing%2C%20soul-crushing%20work.%26quot%3B%20So%20in%202020%2C%20the%20company%20rolled%20out%20a%20new%20feature%3A%20a%20team%20of%20humans%20who%20would%20complete%20your%20job%20applications%20for%20you.%20At%20%2449.97%20a%20month%2C%20it%20proved%20wildly%20popular%3A%20Today%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20applications%20on%20Ladders%20are%20completed%20by%20human%20proxies%20instead%20of%20job%20seekers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELadders'%20decision%20to%20refrain%20from%20fully%20automating%20its%20service%20is%20intentional.%20Cenedella%20says%20his%20team%20has%20taken%20a%20look%20at%20a%20variety%20of%20job-application%20bots.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20we're%20interested%20in%20is%20quality%2C%20accuracy%2C%20and%20speed%2C%26quot%3B%20Cenedella%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BSo%20far%2C%20we%20haven't%20found%20any%20that%20have%20met%20those%20bars%20for%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20we%20know%20how%20this%20story%20goes.%20It's%20as%20old%20as%20John%20Henry.%20Humans%20may%2C%20in%20the%20short%20run%2C%20manage%20to%20beat%20a%20steel-driving%20machine.%20But%20sooner%20or%20later%2C%20their%20hearts%20will%20explode%20from%20trying%20to%20keep%20up.%20The%20humans%20at%20Ladders%20can%20only%20send%20out%2050%20applications%20for%20you%20each%20month.%20But%20the%20job%20bots%20at%20LazyApply%20and%20other%20services%20never%20get%20tired.%20They%20aren't%20aiming%20for%20quality.%20Like%20most%20tech%20these%20days%2C%20they're%20betting%20on%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20smart%20bet.%20Much%20to%20my%20surprise%2C%20out%20of%20the%20126%20jobs%20I%20applied%20to%20with%20the%20bots%2C%20I%20ended%20up%20hearing%20back%20from%20seven%20employers.%20That's%20a%206%25%20success%20rate%20%E2%80%94%20pretty%20high%2C%20considering%20that%20half%20the%20jobs%20were%20in%20areas%20like%20PR%20or%20marketing%2C%20in%20which%20I%20have%20zero%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20responded%20to%20each%20email%20I%20got%20with%20an%20apology%2C%20explaining%20that%20I%20was%20testing%20out%20the%20bots%20for%20a%20story%20I%20was%20writing.%20Did%20the%20employers%20have%20any%20inkling%20that%20my%20application%20came%20from%20a%20bot%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wouldn't%20have%20guessed%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20recruiter%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20way%20to%20know%20on%20LinkedIn%20jobs.%26quot%3B%20Another%20hiring%20manager%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20main%20thing%20that%20was%20unusual%20about%20your%20application%20is%20it%20included%20a%20cover%20letter%20for%20an%20old%20job%20and%20outdated%20CV.%26quot%3B%20Yet%20even%20that%20level%20of%20screw-up%20hadn't%20deterred%20him.%20%26quot%3BOther%20than%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bnothing%20struck%20me%20as%20bot-like%20or%20weird.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20third%20employer%20%E2%80%94%20a%20journalist%20whose%20work%20I've%20admired%20for%20years%20%E2%80%94%20was%20also%20fooled.%20%26quot%3BYikes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20when%20I%20told%20him%20my%20application%20was%20bot-produced.%20%26quot%3BHave%20not%20run%20into%20that%2C%20and%20didn't%20realize.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%2C%20somewhat%20sheepishly%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20on%20a%20cross-country%20plane%20and%20tired.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20duped%20by%20a%20bot%20may%20not%20be%20a%20good%20outcome%20for%20an%20employer%2C%20but%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20win%20for%20me.%20After%20all%2C%20I%20got%20seven%20callbacks%2C%20compared%20with%20the%20zero%20I%20got%20with%20the%20handcrafted%2C%20low-volume%20strategy%20I%20took%20three%20years%20ago%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20bot-driven%20process%20required%20far%20less%20time%20and%20energy.%20Moreover%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20form%20of%20equity.%20Let's%20face%20it%3A%20HR%20departments%20approach%20the%20job-search%20process%20in%20a%20purely%20transactional%20manner%2C%20sending%20out%20automated%20rejections%20to%20desperate%20job%20seekers%20who%20spent%20days%20polishing%20and%20perfecting%20their%20applications.%20Now%20I%20was%20doing%20the%20same%2C%20using%20adaptive%20machines%20to%20get%20my%20human%20foot%20in%20the%20door.%20It%20made%20the%20whole%20shitty%20process%20feel%20a%20bit%20more%20manageable.%20And%20if%20using%20bots%20increases%20your%20odds%20of%20success%2C%20it's%20worth%20a%20shot.%20The%20more%20darts%20you%20throw%20at%20the%20wall%2C%20the%20better%20chance%20you%20have%20of%20hitting%20the%20bull's-eye.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20whatever%20value%20they%20provide%20for%20weary%20job%20seekers%2C%20it's%20worth%20noting%20that%20spray-and-pray%20bots%20don't%20address%20the%20larger%20issue%20that%20prevents%20many%20applicants%20from%20landing%20a%20job.%20Ultimately%2C%20it's%20not%20how%20many%20applications%20you%20send%20out%20that%20wins%20the%20day%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20the%20connections%20you%20have.%20A%20good%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20is%20one%20thing%2C%20but%20if%20Bob%20over%20in%20marketing%20says%20you'd%20be%20a%20great%20addition%20to%20the%20team%2C%20that%20means%20a%20whole%20lot%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20challenge%20for%20job%20seekers%20is%20that%20you%20see%20a%20great%20job%2C%20but%20you%20see%20it%20at%20the%20same%20time%20as%205%20million%20other%20people%20on%20the%20job%20board%2C%26quot%3B%20Emily%20Lamia%2C%20an%20experienced%20career%20coach%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BHow%20you%20find%20out%20about%20those%20jobs%20before%20they're%20listed%2C%20and%20how%20you%20make%20the%20right%20connections%20to%20even%20design%20a%20job%20for%20yourself%2C%20is%20how%20people%20end%20up%20in%20positions%20that%20are%20really%20fulfilling%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%20Lamia%20routinely%20polls%20her%20clients%2C%20and%20she's%20found%20that%2080%25%20of%20the%20time%2C%20they%20got%20their%20current%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20and%20most%20of%20their%20past%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20through%20some%20kind%20of%20connection.%20That's%20why%20she%20says%20she%20would%20never%20recommend%20job-search%20bots%20to%20her%20clients.%20Instead%20of%20cold%20applying%20to%20hundreds%20of%20jobs%2C%20they%20need%20to%20focus%20on%20networking%20for%20the%20ones%20they%20really%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENetworking%20is%20ultimately%20how%20I%20landed%20my%20job%20at%20Business%20Insider.%20My%20original%20cold%20application%20to%20the%20company%20%E2%80%94%20the%20one%20that%20included%20my%20%26quot%3BDear%20Mr.%20Carlson%26quot%3B%20cover%20letter%20%E2%80%94%20went%20nowhere.%20So%20I%20swallowed%20my%20pride%20and%20messaged%20anyone%20I%20knew%20who%20might%20be%20able%20to%20provide%20me%20with%20an%20introduction.%20One%20former%20colleague%20I%20reached%20out%20to%20suggested%20I%20talk%20to%20a%20friend%20of%20his%20at%20BI.%20The%20friend%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20connected%20me%20with%20an%20editor%20there%2C%20who%20then%20introduced%20me%20to%20his%20boss%2C%20who%20passed%20me%20on%20to%20a%20different%20boss%2C%20who%20eventually%20hired%20me.%20Thanks%20to%20those%20introductions%2C%20a%20company%20that%20showed%20zero%20interest%20in%20my%20initial%20application%20offered%20to%20create%20a%20whole%20new%20position%20to%20enable%20me%20to%20report%20on%20the%20rapid%20changes%20unfolding%20in%20the%20American%20workplace.%20No%20bot%20could%20ever%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20I%20came%20away%20from%20my%20time%20among%20the%20job-search%20bots%20feeling%20the%20way%20I%20do%20about%20much%20of%20AI.%20It%20can%20be%20incredibly%20helpful%20for%20plowing%20through%20tedious%20tasks.%20And%20it's%20going%20to%20get%20better%20over%20time.%20But%20for%20now%2C%20you%20have%20to%20keep%20an%20eye%20on%20it.%20At%20the%20moment%2C%20relying%20on%20a%20bot%20is%20like%20turning%20a%20task%20over%20to%20an%20intern.%20They're%20hardworking%20and%20helpful.%20But%20they're%20also%20inexperienced%20and%20underpaid%20%E2%80%94%20so%20you'd%20be%20smart%20to%20check%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-applications-hiring-ai-bots-spam-resume-cover-letter-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709636581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e5ff99ce7f1785b2e5f7e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-applications-hiring-ai-bots-spam-resume-cover-letter-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20used%20AI-powered%20resume%20spammers%20to%20appl