34.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Famericas-massive-multi-state-voting-event-super-tuesday-a-big-day-for-joe-biden-donald-trump-in-us-presidential-elections%2Fphotostory%2F108229813.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F108229813.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Famericas-massive-multi-state-voting-event-super-tuesday-a-big-day-for-joe-biden-donald-trump-in-us-presidential-elections%2Fphotostory%2F108229813.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Has%20the%20Highest%20Rate%20of%20%E2%80%98Zero-Food%E2%80%99%20Children%20After%20Guinea%20and%20Mali%2C%20Reveals%20Study%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F07114756%2Faditya-romansa-5zp0jym2w9M-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%E2%80%99s%20prevalence%20of%20%E2%80%9Czero-food%E2%80%9D%20children%20%E2%80%93%20where%20they%20haven%E2%80%99t%20consumed%20anything%20at%20all%20in%20a%2024-hour%20span%20%E2%80%93%20is%20comparable%20to%20the%20rates%20in%20the%20west%20African%20nations%20of%20Guinea%2C%20Benin%2C%20Liberia%20and%20Mali%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Findias-zero-food-children-shame-6-7m-kids-have-nothing-to-eat-for-entire-day%2Fcid%2F2004741%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20a%20study%20that%20used%20data%20from%20the%20Union%20health%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20National%20Family%20Health%20Survey%20for%202019-2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20estimated%20India%E2%80%99s%20prevalence%20of%20zero-food%20children%20at%2019.3%25%2C%20the%20third%20highest%20after%20Guinea%E2%80%99s%2021.8%25%20and%20Mali%E2%80%99s%2020.5%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20figures%20are%20much%20lower%20in%20Bangladesh%20(5.6%25)%2C%20Pakistan%20(9.2%25)%2C%20DR%20Congo%20(7.4%25)%2C%20Nigeria%20(8.8%25)%20and%20Ethiopia%20(14.8%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20was%20conducted%20using%20health%20surveys%20across%2092%20low-income%20and%20middle-income%20countries%20at%20various%20times%20between%202010%20and%202021.%20The%20research%20was%20conducted%20by%20population%20health%20researcher%20S.V.%20Subramanian%20from%20Harvard%20University%20and%20his%20colleagues%2C%20and%20was%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamanetworkopen%2Ffullarticle%2F2814926%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EJAMA%20Network%20Open%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20peer-reviewed%20journal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20revealed%20that%20South%20Asia%20has%20the%20highest%20prevalence%20of%20zero-food%20children%2C%20estimated%20at%208%20million%2C%20with%20India%20alone%20accounting%20for%20over%206.7%20million%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELack%20of%20feeding%20care%20to%20infants%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHealth%20experts%20familiar%20with%20child%20nutrition%20issues%20in%20India%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20deprivation%20of%20food%20leading%20to%20zero-food%20children%20is%20likely%20to%20reflect%20not%20a%20lack%20of%20access%20to%20food%20but%20the%20inability%20of%20many%20mothers%20to%20provide%20appropriate%20feeding%20care%20to%20their%20infants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZero-food%20children%20are%20infants%20or%20toddlers%20aged%20between%20six%20months%20and%2024%20months%20who%20have%20not%20received%20any%20milk%20or%20solid%20or%20semisolid%20food%20over%20a%2024-hour%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%2092%20countries%2C%20over%2099%25%20of%20the%20zero-food%20children%20had%20been%20breastfed%2C%20indicating%20that%20almost%20all%20the%20children%20had%20received%20some%20calories%20even%20during%20the%2024-hour%20period%20during%20which%20they%20had%20been%20deprived%20of%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20at%20six%20months%2C%20breastfeeding%20is%20no%20longer%20sufficient%20to%20provide%20children%20with%20the%20nutrition%20they%20require%2C%20said%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChildren%20then%20need%20adequate%20protein%2C%20energy%2C%20vitamins%20and%20minerals%20through%20additional%20food%20along%20with%20breastfeeding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20numbers%20highlight%E2%80%A6%20the%20urgent%20need%20for%20tailored%20interventions%20to%20address%20this%20issue%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Subramanian%20and%20his%20colleagues%20said%20in%20their%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20said%20that%20more%20research%20was%20needed%20to%20unravel%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20underlying%20causes%E2%80%9D%20of%20zero-food%20prevalence%2C%20the%20barriers%20to%20optimal%20adequate%20child-feeding%20practices%2C%20and%20the%20ways%20socioeconomic%20factors%20might%20influence%20child-feeding%20behaviour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVandana%20Prasad%2C%20a%20paediatrician%20and%20public%20health%20specialist%20who%20was%20not%20associated%20with%20the%20study%2C%20told%20the%20daily%20that%20many%20infants%20and%20toddlers%20are%20deprived%20of%20complementary%20feeding%20because%20their%20mothers%E2%80%99%20circumstances%20prevent%20them%20from%20providing%20the%20children%20with%20feeding%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20not%20easy%20to%20feed%20children%20who%20are%20six%20months%20old%20%E2%80%93%20it%20takes%20time%20and%20energy%2C%20and%20many%20of%20the%20women%20in%20households%20where%20zero-food%20children%20might%20have%20been%20found%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20support%20they%20require%20for%20adequate%20complementary%20feeding%2C%E2%80%9D%20Prasad%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20economically%20disadvantaged%20households%2C%20whether%20in%20rural%20regions%20or%20urban%20slums%2C%20mothers%20often%20find%20themselves%20balancing%20responsibilities%20to%20earn%20wages%20and%20carry%20out%20household%20chores.%20This%20leaves%20them%20with%20insufficient%20time%20to%20dedicate%20to%20complementary%20feeding%20for%20their%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaternity%20entitlements%20and%20childcare%20services%20could%20help%20address%20the%20issue%20but%20many%20women%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20access%20to%20such%20services%2C%20said%20Prasad%2C%20who%E2%80%99s%20also%20a%20technical%20adviser%20to%20the%20Public%20Health%20Resource%20Network%2C%20a%20non-government%20agency%20that%20has%20shown%20through%20studies%20in%20Odisha%20how%20cr%C3%A8ches%20can%20help%20reduce%20under-nutrition%20levels%20in%20children%20from%20vulnerable%20households.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECultural%20issues%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20information%2C%20too%2C%20may%20in%20some%20instances%20affect%20complementary%20feeding%20practices%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFindings%20from%20the%20previous%20study%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubramanian%20and%20his%20colleagues%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Ftwo-out-of-10-infants-face-risk-of-food-deprivation-says-survey%2Fcid%2F1927832%5C%22%3Ehad%20last%20year%20generated%3C%2Fa%3E%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20estimate%20of%20the%20prevalence%20of%20zero-food%20children%2C%20based%20on%20the%202019-2021%20health%20survey%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20revealed%20that%20nearly%20two%20among%20every%2010%20infants%20or%20toddlers%20in%20India%20face%20the%20risk%20of%20not%20receiving%20any%20food%20whatsoever%20for%20a%20full%20day%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Ftwo-out-of-10-infants-face-risk-of-food-deprivation-says-survey%2Fcid%2F1927832%5C%22%3Ehad%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%20And%20this%20revealed%20virtually%20no%20change%20in%20this%20measure%20of%20food%20deprivation%20since%202016%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20percentage%20of%20%E2%80%9Czero-food%E2%80%9D%20children%20increased%20from%2017.2%25%20in%202016%20to%2017.8%25%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sampled%20children%20were%20aged%20between%20six%20months%20and%2023%20months%20who%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20eaten%20any%20food%20with%20substantial%20calorific%20content%20for%20at%20least%20an%20entire%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20data%20contained%20something%20unusual%20and%20unexpected%20%E2%80%94%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20expect%20young%20children%20between%20six%20months%20and%2023%20months%20to%20go%20entirely%20unfed%20for%20a%20whole%2024%20hours%2C%E2%80%9D%20Subramanian%20had%20told%20the%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20long%20the%20deprivation%20lasted%20in%20each%20child%20sampled%20%E2%80%94%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20limitation%20in%20the%20data.%20But%20we%E2%80%99d%20expect%20a%20child%20to%20receive%20at%20least%20some%20food%20over%20a%20whole%20day%2C%E2%80%9D%20Subramanian%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20absence%20signals%20severe%20food%20deprivation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20study%20sampled%20over%20600%2C000%20households%2C%20and%20included%20questions%20that%20probed%20what%20food%20children%20aged%20six%20to%2023%20months%20had%20consumed%20over%20the%20previous%2024%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%202016%20and%202021%20surveys%20had%20multiple%20identical%20questions%20asking%20whether%20the%20child%20had%20consumed%20any%20of%20a%20variety%20of%20solid%20or%20liquid%20foods.%20An%20answer%20of%20%E2%80%9Cno%E2%80%9D%20to%20all%20the%20food%20questions%20for%20a%20child%20meant%20the%20child%20received%20no%20food%20in%20the%20preceding%2024%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20the%20analysis%20has%20yielded%20an%20estimated%20headcount%20of%205.9%20million%20zero-food%20children%20in%20the%20six-23%20months%20age%20group%20in%20India%20in%202021.%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20had%20the%20highest%20prevalence%20(27.4%25)%20of%20zero-food%20children%2C%20followed%20by%20Chhattisgarh%20(24.6%25)%2C%20Jharkhand%20(21%25)%2C%20Rajasthan%20(19.8%25)%2C%20and%20Assam%20(19.4%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBengal%20is%20one%20of%20around%2020%20states%20where%20the%20prevalence%20of%20zero-food%20children%20has%20decreased%20since%202016.%20In%20Bengal%20specifically%2C%20the%20proportion%20dropped%20from%2012.1%25%20in%202016%20to%207.5%25%20in%202021%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoa%20had%20the%20most%20substantial%20drop%20from%2018.9%25%20to%205.1%25%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20study%20was%20published%20in%20%3Cem%3EeClinicalMedicine%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20member%20of%20The%20Lancet%20family%20of%20journals.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709623827000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F07114756%2Faditya-romansa-5zp0jym2w9M-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Findia-has-the-highest-rate-of-zero-food-children-after-guinea-and-mali-reveals-study%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20study%20estimated%20the%20prevalence%20of%20zero-food%20children%20%E2%80%93%20where%20they%20haven't%20consumed%20anything%20at%20all%20in%20a%2024-hour%20span%20%E2%80%93%20in%20India%20is%20at%2019.3%25.%20The%20figures%20are%20much%20lower%20in%20Bangladesh%20(5.6%25)%2C%20Pakistan%20(9.2%25)%2C%20DR%20Congo%20(7.4%25)%2C%20Nigeria%20(8.8%25)%20and%20Ethiopia%20(14.8%25).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Findia-has-the-highest-rate-of-zero-food-children-after-guinea-and-mali-reveals-study%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Director%20Miguel%20Marti%2C%20Actress-Producer%20Macarena%20Gomez%20Launch%20Online%20Hunt%20For%20Horror%20Scripts%20With%20Spanish%20Tinge%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709623080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fva